'''Peter Till''' (born 7 September 1985) is an English [[association football|footballer]] who plays for [[York City F.C.|York City]] as a [[midfielder#Winger|winger]].

Till started his career with the [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]] [[youth system]] before making his [[first team]] debut in 2005. He was [[loan (association football)|loaned]] to [[Scunthorpe United F.C.|Scunthorpe United]], [[Boston United F.C.|Boston United]], [[Leyton Orient F.C.|Leyton Orient]] and [[Grimsby Town F.C.|Grimsby Town]], whom he joined permanently in 2007. Till made an appearance at [[Wembley Stadium]] in the [[Football League Trophy]] [[2008 Football League Trophy Final|Final]] in 2008 and was loaned to [[Chesterfield F.C.|Chesterfield]] in 2009. He was released after making over 80 appearances for Grimsby and subsequently joined hometown club [[Walsall F.C.|Walsall]]. Being released after one season with the club, he joined York City of the [[Conference National]].

==Career==

===Birmingham City===
Born in [[Walsall]], [[West Midlands (county)|West Midlands]],<ref name=Hugman2008/> Till came through the [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]] [[youth system]] after joining the club as a schoolboy and he earned a two-year [[professional]] contract in the summer of 2005.<ref name="Town v Grimsby Town">{{cite news
| title = Town v Grimsby Town
| url = http://www.shrewsburytown.com/page/PreMatchAnalysis/0,,10443~1486243,00.html
| publisher = Shrewsbury Town F.C.
| date = 12 December 2008
| accessdate = 22 July 2010}}</ref> He was included in the matchday [[first team]] squad on a few occasions during the [[2004<U+2013>05 in English football|2004<U+2013>05]] season,<ref name="Boston United Squad 2005/2006">{{cite web
| title = Boston United Squad 2005/2006
| url = http://www.bufc.drfox.org.uk/squad05.html
| publisher = Boston United FC - The Original Website
| accessdate = 22 July 2010}}</ref> with Academy manager Stewart Hall commenting "When he has trained and worked with the first team he has looked very good and he has had an excellent season in the reserves and looked a real threat".<ref name="The young ones: Academy end of term report">{{cite web
| title = The young ones: Academy end of term report
| url = http://www.bcfc.com/page/News/NewsDetail/0,,10412~664613,00.html
| publisher = Birmingham City F.C.
| accessdate = 22 July 2010}}</ref> He made his debut in a 2<U+2013>0 victory over [[Football League One|League One]] team [[Scunthorpe United F.C.|Scunthorpe United]] in the [[Football League Cup|League Cup]] on 20 September 2005.<ref name="Scunthorpe 0-2 Birmingham">{{cite news
